New book 'Reenactment MfS' is a collection of pictures taken by the Stasi - East Germany's secret police - of people trying to escape the country . 
  Families were forced to pose for the pictures which were used as 'evidence' in show trials . 
  The pictures were also used to train border guards and trainee agents . 
  They were found in the archives of the Ministry for State Security . 
 